         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">14/4/76. ¶  ¶ It is quite wonderful, dear Mr Bentham, to watch you working. I trust, however, that you not overstrain your nervous system. Do not distress yourself about the Liliaceae &amp;c in your hand;...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">76.04.14</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-81, f. 175.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, ﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, ﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS black edged; M's brother-in-law, Eduard Wehl, died on 11 February 1876.</p>
               </note>14/4/76.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, ﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is quite wonderful, dear Mr Bentham, to watch you working. I trust, however, that you not overstrain your nervous system. Do not distress yourself about the <name key="Liliaceae">Liliaceae</name> &amp;c in your hand; as I said before the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">genera</hi>
               </seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, ﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862–83).</p>
               </note> are far more important than the Austr. Fl.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, ﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham (1863-78). Bentham had just shipped M's <name key="Liliaceae">Liliaceae</name> back to Australia; see G. Bentham to M, 13 April 1876 (in this edition as 76-04-13a).</p>
               </note> Though of course occasional inconvenience does arise, if a large portion of the main collection is long away, yet for all that you ought not be troubled. Let me gratulate you to your long merited election in the French Academy.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, ﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham was elected a Corresponding Member of the Paris Academy of Sciences on 24 May 1875, in succession to Alphonse de Candolle, following the latter's promotion to Associé Étranger (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Index biographique des membres de l'Académie des Sciences …</seg> (Paris, 1978)).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, ﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful remembrance</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, ﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, ﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Now rather more than half a thousand additional species (for vol I-VI)<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, ﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Of Bentham (1863-73).<seg style=""> </seg>For a discussion of the failure to publish the proposed supplements to <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Flora australiensis,</seg> see Clements (1998) and Lucas (2003)<seg style="">.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> are described in the fragmenta. I trust in time to bring the additions up to a full thousand.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <name key="Liliaceae">Liliaceae</name>
            </p>
         </div>
